HTML allows you to specify a starting number from which an ordered list (&lt;ol&gt;) should start. I thought &ldquo;Is there an upper bound?&rdquo;.
Turns out: Yes, there is. It&rsquo;s 2147483647 (i.e. 231-1). No idea why it&rsquo;s not 232-1, though &hellip;
&lt;ol start=2147483645&gt; &lt;li&gt;I am still in order&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;As am I&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Me too&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Limit reached&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Limit reached&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Limit reached&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt; The above snippet will render as the following:

All you need is the secret of your TOTP.
The QR code is just a representation of a oath:// URL That URL contains the secret as a query parameter.
# Install oathtool brew install oathtool # Use your secret, e.g. as a base32-encoded string oathtool --totp --base32 &#34;MFRGCZDTMVRXEZLUBI======&#34;
